  <span id="freeText10946623047383670442" style="display:none">Focused almost exclusively on the now infamous 1948 Senate primary, which LBJ stole from conservative former governor of Texas, Coke Stevenson, this is the shortest of the four volumes but likely the most riveting. This reads like a political thriller that won't let you put it down.</span>
