<div id="review_2781158159" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2781158159" />
    <a title="Mack Hayden" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6036690-mack-hayden"><img alt="Mack Hayden" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1498610629p2/6036690.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2781158159?book_show_action=true">May 01, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mack Hayden" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mack Hayden" href="/user/show/6036690-mack-hayden">Mack Hayden</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6036690-mack-hayden?shelf=politics">politics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6036690-mack-hayden?shelf=biography">biography</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6036690-mack-hayden?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6036690-mack-hayden?shelf=america">america</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2781158159" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15467622828087528419">Caro keeps the car running brilliantly in this second installment. On the one hand, it&apos;s an almost impossibly comprehensive chronicle of Johnson&apos;s years between losing one Senate race and stealing another, as well as a terrific general account of the era. But on the other, as with the first, this book is a study in the ways ambition and the hunger for power function in America even to this day. Johnson would take any position, tell any lie, make any underhanded deal he could to move upward on th</span>
  <span id="freeText15467622828087528419" style="display:none">Caro keeps the car running brilliantly in this second installment. On the one hand, it's an almost impossibly comprehensive chronicle of Johnson's years between losing one Senate race and stealing another, as well as a terrific general account of the era. But on the other, as with the first, this book is a study in the ways ambition and the hunger for power function in America even to this day. Johnson would take any position, tell any lie, make any underhanded deal he could to move upward on the social ladder. Even as Caro paints him in his towering deceitfulness, he manages to convey his humanity in such a way that he doesn't come across as a villain. It's a book both damning and celebratory of the good, the bad, and the ugly of Lyndon Johnson and the country that made him.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15467622828087528419" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


