<div id="review_3679042619" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3679042619" />
    <a title="Glen Bowman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23399742-glen-bowman"><img alt="Glen Bowman" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3679042619?book_show_action=true">Jan 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Glen Bowman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Glen Bowman" href="/user/show/23399742-glen-bowman">Glen Bowman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3679042619" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13963637574312451199">Like Path to Power this is detailed rich history. It is very critical of LBJ, but the author warns us at the outset that LBJs life was interwoven strands of good and bad , but that there would not be good in this volume. His opponent in the 1948 Senate race that he allegedly stole, Coke Stephenson, is made to seem almost inhumanly righteous by Caro. So much so that it became impossible to believe. There was nothing this man did that was not bigger than life. <br/>That said, Caro is clearly a master b</span>
  <span id="freeText13963637574312451199" style="display:none">Like Path to Power this is detailed rich history. It is very critical of LBJ, but the author warns us at the outset that LBJs life was interwoven strands of good and bad , but that there would not be good in this volume. His opponent in the 1948 Senate race that he allegedly stole, Coke Stephenson, is made to seem almost inhumanly righteous by Caro. So much so that it became impossible to believe. There was nothing this man did that was not bigger than life. <br />That said, Caro is clearly a master biographer. One wonders how he could spend so much of his life and talent on a man he clearly believes was deeply flawed and unworthy - who reached America’s political summit by actually stealing an election. <br />Moving on to Master of the Senate!</span>
  <a data-text-id="13963637574312451199" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


